\
     ## Critical Facts Discovered\
\
     1. **Pipeline DID run.** Run `b3ef903b472d` exists in `~/Q/conductor/.conductor/runs/`, status `awaiting_approval`. Worker `qwen` generated a valid 3-node plan. The "never ran end-to-end" premise was wrong.\
     2. **`rvc project init` exists** but creates a `vault/` subdirectory inside target. It does NOT create `.obsidian/`.\
     3. **`rvc rescan` is dangerous** вАГі injects non-semantic bulk wikilinks. Never run it on curated vaults.\
     4. **Path schizophrenia:** `adlai.toml` points to `~/Documents/ADLAI`, workspace uses `~/Q/GATHERING/ADLAI` (same dir via symlinks, but Conductor/RVC may resolve differently).\
     5. **Cross-vault ID collision:** ADLAI uses `STORY-01..99`, RVC uses `STORY-001..014`. We must use `FLOW-` prefix in flow-vault.\
     6. **`rvc` commands work from `flow-vault/`** but NOT from `GATHERING/` (fails to find vault dir when nested).\
\
     ## Files Created\
\
     - `~/Q/GATHERING/flow-vault/vault/10_Issues/02_Active/EPIC-FLOW-001.md` вАГі replacement epic with reality check\
     - `~/Q/GATHERING/flow-vault/vault/10_Issues/02_Active/STORY-FLOW-001.md` вАГі first active story: restructure layout & harden init\
\
